#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.72"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.72:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.72:0.2"
msgid "8. Ākaṅkhavagga"
msgstr "8. If You Want"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.72:0.3"
msgid "72. Kaṇṭakasutta"
msgstr "72. Thorns"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.72:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ sambahulehi "
"abhiññātehi abhiññātehi therehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ—"
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof, together with several well-known senior disciples."

#. VAR: cālena → pālena (s1-3) | cāḷena (pts1)
#. VAR: upacālena → upapālena (s1-3)
#. VAR: kukkuṭena → kakkaṭena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: kaḷimbhena → katimbhena (bj)
#. VAR: nikaṭena → kaṭena (bj)
msgctxt "an10.72:1.2"
msgid ""
"āyasmatā ca cālena, āyasmatā ca upacālena, āyasmatā ca kukkuṭena, āyasmatā "
"ca kaḷimbhena, āyasmatā ca nikaṭena, āyasmatā ca kaṭissahena;"
msgstr ""
"They included Venerables Cāla, Upacāla, Kakkaṭa, Kaṭimbha, Kaṭa, Kaṭissaṅga,"

msgctxt "an10.72:1.3"
msgid "aññehi ca abhiññātehi abhiññātehi therehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ."
msgstr "and other well-known senior disciples."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.134"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: parapurāya → carapurāya (bj, pts1) | paramparāya (s1-3) | parampurāya (s-a)
msgctxt "an10.72:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī bhadrehi "
"bhadrehi yānehi parapurāya uccāsaddā mahāsaddā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhanti "
"bhagavantaṃ dassanāya."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time several well-known Licchavis plunged deep into the Great "
"Wood to see the Buddha. Driving a succession of fine carriages, they made a "
"dreadful racket."

msgctxt "an10.72:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then those venerables thought:"

msgctxt "an10.72:2.3"
msgid ""
"“ime kho sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi "
"parapurāya uccāsaddā mahāsaddā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhanti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya."
msgstr ""
"“These several well-known Licchavis have plunged deep into the Great Wood to "
"see the Buddha. Driving a succession of fine carriages, they’re making a "
"dreadful racket."

msgctxt "an10.72:2.4"
msgid "Saddakaṇṭakā kho pana jhānā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "But the Buddha has said that sound is a thorn to absorption."

msgctxt "an10.72:2.5"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkameyyāma."
msgstr "Let’s go to the Gosiṅga Sal Wood."

#. VAR: phāsuṃ → phāsu (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an10.72:2.6"
msgid "Tattha mayaṃ appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ vihareyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "There we can meditate comfortably, free of noise and crowds.”"

msgctxt "an10.72:2.7"
msgid "Atha kho te āyasmanto yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "Then those venerables went to the Gosiṅga Sal Wood,"

msgctxt "an10.72:2.8"
msgid "tattha te āyasmanto appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ viharanti."
msgstr "where they meditated comfortably, free of noise and crowds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.72:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an10.72:3.2"
msgid ""
"“kahaṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, cālo, kahaṃ upacālo, kahaṃ kukkuṭo, kahaṃ "
"kaḷimbho, kahaṃ nikaṭo, kahaṃ kaṭissaho;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, where are Cāla, Upacāla, Kakkaṭa, Kaṭimbha, Kaṭa, and "
"Kaṭissaṅga?"

msgctxt "an10.72:3.3"
msgid "kahaṃ nu kho te, bhikkhave, therā sāvakā gatā”ti?"
msgstr "Where have these senior disciples gone?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.72:4.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhante, tesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "And the mendicants told him what had happened."

msgctxt "an10.72:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime kho sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi "
"parapurāya uccāsaddā mahāsaddā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhanti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya "
"saddakaṇṭakā kho pana jhānā vuttā bhagavatā yannūna mayaṃ yena "
"gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkameyyāma tattha mayaṃ appasaddā appākiṇṇā "
"phāsuṃ vihareyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.72:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te, bhante, āyasmanto yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.72:4.4"
msgid "Tattha te āyasmanto appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.72:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, yathā te mahāsāvakā sammā byākaramānā byākareyyuṃ, "
"saddakaṇṭakā hi, bhikkhave, jhānā vuttā mayā."
msgstr ""
"“Good, good, mendicants! It’s just as those great disciples have so rightly "
"explained. I have said that sound is a thorn to absorption."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.135"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.72:6.1"
msgid "Dasayime, bhikkhave, kaṇṭakā."
msgstr "Mendicants, there are these ten thorns."

msgctxt "an10.72:6.2"
msgid "Katame dasa?"
msgstr "What ten?"

#. VAR: brahmacariyassa → brahmacārissa (bj)
#. VAR: mātugāmūpacāro → mātugāmopavicāro (bj, pts1) | mātugāmūpavicaro (mr)
msgctxt "an10.72:6.3"
msgid ""
"Pavivekārāmassa saṅgaṇikārāmatā kaṇṭako, asubhanimittānuyogaṃ anuyuttassa "
"subhanimittānuyogo kaṇṭako, indriyesu guttadvārassa visūkadassanaṃ kaṇṭako, "
"brahmacariyassa mātugāmūpacāro kaṇṭako, paṭhamassa jhānassa saddo kaṇṭako, "
"dutiyassa jhānassa vitakkavicārā kaṇṭakā, tatiyassa jhānassa pīti kaṇṭako, "
"catutthassa jhānassa assāsapassāso kaṇṭako, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā "
"saññā ca vedanā ca kaṇṭako rāgo kaṇṭako doso kaṇṭako moho kaṇṭako."
msgstr ""
"Relishing company is a thorn for someone who loves seclusion. Focusing on "
"the beautiful aspect of things is a thorn for someone pursuing the "
"meditation on ugliness. Seeing shows is a thorn to someone restraining the "
"senses. Lingering in the neighborhood of females is a thorn to celibacy. "
"Sound is a thorn to the first absorption. Placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected are a thorn to the second absorption. Rapture is a thorn to the "
"third absorption. Breathing is a thorn to the fourth absorption. Perception "
"and feeling are a thorn to the attainment of the cessation of perception and "
"feeling. Greed, hate, and delusion are thorns."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an10.72:7.1"
msgid "Akaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, viharatha."
msgstr "Mendicants, live free of thorns!"

msgctxt "an10.72:7.2"
msgid "Nikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, viharatha."
msgstr "Live rid of thorns!"

msgctxt "an10.72:7.3"
msgid "Akaṇṭakanikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, viharatha."
msgstr "Mendicants, live free of thorns and rid of thorns!"

msgctxt "an10.72:7.4"
msgid "Akaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, arahanto;"
msgstr "The perfected ones live free of thorns,"

msgctxt "an10.72:7.5"
msgid "nikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, arahanto;"
msgstr "rid of thorns,"

msgctxt "an10.72:7.6"
msgid "akaṇṭakanikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, arahanto”ti."
msgstr "free and rid of thorns.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.72:7.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
